OCCASIONAL notes on scansion are given here, in cases likely to cause difficulty. A knowledge of the ordinary phenomena of Plautiae prosody is assumed. The terms ‘ rise ’ and ‘ fall ’ are here employed instead of arsis and thesis, which have become so confused in nse as no longer to suggest any definite idea. ‘ Rise ' and ‘ fall ’ correspond to the con- venient German terms Hebung and Senkung—denoting respectively the crest and the trough of a wave of sound.
